{
  "date": "2026-03-27",
  "title": "Entrusted, Not Excused",
  "scriptures": [
    {
      "ref": "Matthew 25:14-30",
      "text": "The Parable of the Talents"
    },
    {
      "ref": "Proverbs 6:6-8",
      "text": "The Ant and diligence"
    }
  ],
  "sections": [
    {
      "key": "read_this_out_loud",
      "label": "Read This Out Loud",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You don’t own it."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But you are responsible for it."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "What you’ve been given matters."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And what you do with it…. matters more."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "God is not looking for perfection."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He’s looking for faithfulness."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_devotional",
      "label": "The Devotional",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Most men live like managers."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "Maintain.",
            "Protect.",
            "Play it safe.",
            "Do enough to avoid loss."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But Jesus tells a different story."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "A master entrusts his servants with resources."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not equally…."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "but intentionally."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And then he leaves."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "No micromanaging.",
            "No daily check-ins.",
            "No reminders.",
            "Just responsibility."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Two servants take what they were given…."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "and multiply it."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "One buries it."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Not out of rebellion…."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "but out of fear."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And that’s what makes it dangerous."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because from the outside,"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "he looks responsible."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "But underneath,"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "he’s disconnected from trust."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_shift",
      "label": "The Shift",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Managers try not to lose."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Owners multiply."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Managers think:"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "“How do I protect what I have?”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Owners think:"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "“How do I grow what I’ve been given?”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And the difference isn’t skill…."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It’s mindset."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It’s identity."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It’s trust."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because buried potential doesn’t just stay neutral…."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "it creates drift"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "it creates doubt"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "it creates distance"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Unused calling always turns into internal tension."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "proverbs_reveals_the_pattern",
      "label": "Proverbs Reveals the Pattern",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "“Go to the ant….” (Proverbs 6:6)"
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "No overseer.",
            "No accountability partner.",
            "No one watching."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Yet it prepares."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It builds."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It stores."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Why?"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Because ownership doesn’t need pressure."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "It’s internal."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "the_truth",
      "label": "The Truth",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "God is not asking:"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "“How much were you given?”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "He’s asking:"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "“What did you do with it?”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You don’t answer for someone else’s calling."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "You answer for yours."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And doing nothing…."
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "is not neutral."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "It’s disobedience dressed as caution."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "jesus_is_calling_this_out",
      "label": "Jesus Is Calling This Out",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "“Well done, good and faithful servant….”"
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "Not successful.",
            "Not impressive."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Faithful."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Faithfulness is measured by movement."
        },
        {
          "type": "lines",
          "items": [
            "Not perfection.",
            "Not comparison."
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "Movement."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "reflection",
      "label": "Reflection",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "Where have I buried what God gave me?",
            "Where am I playing it safe instead of stepping up?",
            "What have I been entrusted with that I’ve treated casually?",
            "Am I thinking like a manager…. or an owner?"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "declaration",
      "label": "Declaration",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I am entrusted, not excused."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "What God has given me, I will steward with intention."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I choose faithfulness over fear."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "I will multiply what’s in my hands."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "action_step",
      "label": "Action Step",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Take inventory today."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Write down 3 things God has entrusted to you:"
        },
        {
          "type": "bullet_list",
          "items": [
            "time",
            "relationships",
            "skills",
            "opportunities"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Then ask:"
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "prefix": "👉",
          "text": "“What would it look like to multiply this?”"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "And act on one."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "key": "one_sentence_to_carry",
      "label": "One Sentence to Carry",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "quote",
          "text": "“What I’ve been given isn’t mine to keep, it’s mine to multiply.” -TheWrkShop"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "__insert_block_header": "2026-03-27_matthew-25-14-30_entrusted-not-excused|"
}
